The paper focuses on automated bug fixing, which is a software engineering problem (cs.SE). It also involves learning from past fixes, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach uses a clustering algorithm, which could also be related to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the approach in terms of its impact on software reliability, which could be considered a security and cryptography issue (cs.CR).
